{
  "texts": [
    "Robust data access controls must be implemented to allow only authenticated and authorized users to access the data and ensure security.",
    "Additionally, distributed data storage solutions should be employed to mitigate the risk of single points of failure during attacks or node failures, thereby enhancing the resilience and reliability of the system.",
    "As AI tasks on the network have become increasingly complex, the number of parameters, data volume, and computing resources required by AI models have dramatically increased (Gill et al., 2022).",
    "The capabilities of a single network node are usually insufficient for training such models, which has increased the demand for distributed learning algorithms.",
    "Different from information technology (IT) computing clusters, a mobile network is an integrated system comprising distributed devices from multiple vendors."
  ]
}